import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='net_generation', hue='source', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend in net generation over the years?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(title='Source')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['renewable'] = data['source'].apply(lambda x: 'Renewable' if x == 'Renewables' else 'Non-Renewable')
    renewable_data = data.groupby('renewable')['net_generation'].sum().reset_index()

    plt.pie(renewable_data['net_generation'], labels=renewable_data['renewable'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the proportion of net generation from renewable sources?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(renewable_data['renewable'], loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.barplot(x='year', y='net_generation', hue='source', data=data, ci=None)

    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;
